The English Premier League on Friday announced the eight nominees for the Young Player of the 2021/22 Season. The eight players are Trent Alexander-Arnold, Bukayo Saka, Phil Foden, Conor Gallagher, Tyrick Mitchell, Mason Mount, Aaron Ramsdale and Declan Rice. The English-top flight league made the announcement in a statement via its website. Fans have until 18:00 BST on Monday 16 May to vote for their favourite aged 23 or younger. The votes from the public will be combined with those of a panel of football experts to decide the winner. Meanwhile, EPL has already shortlisted nominees for the Player of the Season and Manager of the Season.